Here's how to handle each scenario in MSTest:

## 1. Windows-Only (Platform Condition)

```csharp
// MSTest v3+ has no built-in [OSCondition], so use a helper:
[TestMethod]
public void RegistryTest()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows.");
        return;
    }

    // ... registry code
}
```

Or filter by category:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("WindowsOnly")]
public void RegistryTest() { /* ... */ }
```

Then exclude in CI on Linux: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=WindowsOnly"`

## 2. Skip in CI (Environment Check)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void GpuRenderTest()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU.");
        return;
    }

    // ... GPU test
}
```

Or simply filter in your CI pipeline: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"`

## 3. Flaky External API (Retry)

MSTest v3+ has a built-in `[Retry]` attribute:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)] // retries up to 3 times on failure
public void WeatherApiFetchTest()
{
    var result = WeatherClient.GetForecast("Seattle");
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

## 4. Cleanup Even on Failure (TestCleanup)

```csharp
[TestClass]
public class TempFileTests
{
    private string _tempFile = null!;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestCleanup]
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        // Runs even if the test fails or throws
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void WriteTempDataTest()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "test data");
        Assert.IsTrue(File.Exists(_tempFile));
    }
}
```

---

**Summary:**

| Scenario | Approach |
|----------|----------|
| Platform-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` guard or `[TestCategory]` + filter |
| Skip in CI | Environment variable check or `--filter` exclusion |
| Flaky/external | `[Retry(N)]` (MSTest v3+) |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` method |
